article.headline: Texas State 93, Central Arkansas 80
article.story: SAN MARCOS, Texas (AP) -- Brandon Bush scored 25 points and Brent Holder added 19 to give Texas State a 93-80 win over Central Arkansas on Saturday. Bush was 5-of-9 from the field and was a perfect 12-for-12 at the free throw line for the Bobcats (7-8, 2-0 Southland). Holder, coming off the bench, was 6-for-9 from the field and hit three 3-pointers. After trailing 46-32 at halftime, Central Arkansas (5-10, 0-2) managed a 15-4 run that cut Texas State's lead to 59-54 with 11:27 remaining, but the Bears got no closer. Nate Bowie led UCA with 18 points. Durrell Nevels added 12 points and grabbed 13 rebounds.
